<br>
They came to my attention when I found myself inexplicably buffed several times - and with the area lively with Specs, SGs and Lockjaw you can imagine how useful this was to me soloing.<br>
<br>
It wasn't until the 2nd time that I found it was Ailiana who had done this. I thanked her for her gifts but she dismissed her help as a small thing, claiming that I had often in the past buffed her with Breeze as I was passing. She immediately went on to offer me the many gems she had collected as loot, insisting she had no use for them. I left the sisters hunting together, both on my friends list.<br>
<br>
Half an hour later Ailiana sends me a tell - she had seen me run past a few times on my own, was I happy soloing or would I care to join them? This seemed to me a wholly unlooked for and generous act. The three of us had huge amounts of fun until a Spec finished off Ailiana and I both - and Ailiana was bound in SK.<br>
<br>
This is where I learned something of her previous character - a 27th level Necro. More than that, she AND her sister had been a pair of Necro twins (ye gods, I thought, the men of land go completely soft over chicks with big weapons..this pair would have been utterly irresistable). Ailiana was lucky enough to have a 51st level Heretic friend to bring her back - and she asked if I would care to be rezzed as well so as not to lose my hard won experience. I declined her offer (for no good reason I could figure out afterwards..I just have a independent streak about..oh, say..a few miles wide).<br>
<br>
Unexpected buffs, loot offered, heroic companionship, hilaroius fun and corpse assistance - wow.<br>
<br>
<br>
'Stealth Buffing' has been a pastime of mine since I got Breeze...the look on the faces of casters old and young as a'light breeze fills their mind', the often shouted 'thank you, whoever you are' and the occasional 'many thanks Gladriel' makes me delighted to be an Enchanter. And I'm especially delighted that it brought me into contact with such a fine and fascinating pair as Ailiana and Saqqara.<br>
<br>
Gladriel<br>
